- `MoreFiles.asCharSource(file, encoding).read().toCharArray();`:
  Copies the file content first to a `StringBuilder`, then to a `String` and finally to the `char[]`.
- 
      StringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder();
      MoreFiles.asCharSource(file, encoding).copyTo(sb);
      char[] result = new char[sb.length()];
      sb.getChars(0, sb.length(), result, 0);
   Verbose, non-obvious to write and read, especially because of `getChars` modifying its parameter.

By adding a method `char[] readToCharArray()` to `CharSource` this would be nicely solved. Other implementations of `CharSource` such as `CharSequenceCharSource` could even provide optimized versions of this method.
